Assessment of Urban Green Space Accessibility and Its Role in Climate Resilience: A Case Study of Ibadan City.
•	Objectives:
o	To evaluate the spatial distribution of urban green spaces.
o	To assess the accessibility of green spaces to different socio-economic groups.
o	To analyze the role of green spaces in mitigating climate-related risks such as heatwaves and flooding.
•	Methodology:
o	Use GIS tools to map green spaces and calculate accessibility indices.
o	Conduct surveys to gather public opinions on green space usage.
o	Analyze climatic data to correlate green space presence with urban temperature variations.